First, we need to find the symmetric difference (A ∆ B) which is the set of elements that are in either A or B, but not in both. 

A ∆ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B)

The union of A and B (A ∪ B) is the set of all elements that are in A or B:

A ∪ B = {2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 9}

The intersection of A and B (A ∩ B) is the set of all elements that are in both A and B:

A ∩ B = {6}

Now, we can find the symmetric difference:

A ∆ B = {2, 3, 4, 6, 8, 9} - {6} = {2, 3, 4, 8, 9}

Finally, we need to find the union of (A ∆ B) and {8, 9}:

(A ∆ B) ∪ {8, 9} = {2, 3, 4, 8, 9} ∪ {8, 9} = {2, 3, 4, 8, 9}

So, (A ∆ B) ∪ {8, 9} = {2, 3, 4, 8, 9}.
